<HEADLINE>
<P>
PLAN TO EASE TRAFFIC NEAR HIGH SCHOOL OKD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANN GRIFFITH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Rancho Palos Verdes City Council unanimously approved a plan this week to 
help ease traffic congestion near Palos Verdes Peninsula High School on Silver 
Spur Road. 
</P>
<P>
 After complaints from residents living on nearby Basswood Avenue, city 
officials agreed Tuesday to construct a driveway that will line up with the 
avenue. The city estimates that the project will cost $800,000 and will include 
a sidewalk on Silver Spur Road and a new traffic signal. 
</P>
<P>
 Eastbound traffic on Montemalaga Drive will continue to be prohibited from 
turning right onto Basswood Avenue. ANN GRIFFITH 
</P>
</TEXT>
