<P>
BRIEFLY; ARTS: ACTRESS NAMED TO HEAD PEPPERDINE GUILD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Actress Barbara Billingsley has been named president of Pepperdine 
University's Center for the Arts Guild. 
</P>
<P>
 Billingsley is best known for her role as June Cleaver in the television 
series "Leave It To Beaver." The longtime Malibu resident recently completed 
taping for a "Murphy Brown" episode. 
</P>
<P>
 The Center for the Art Guild was founded last year to ensure support of the 
university's arts programs. The guild funds special theater performances, art 
exhibitions and museum tours for school children. 
</P>
