<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: HOLLYWOOD; MAN DIES AFTER 23-STORY FALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man died this week when he apparently leaped from a 23rd floor window at a 
Holiday Inn into a pool. 
</P>
<P>
 The unidentified man opened a window next to the elevators and jumped at about 
1:25 p.m. Sunday into about five feet of water. He was pulled from the pool in 
cardiac arrest and died en route to the hospital, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 "The impact killed him. He may have ruptured his aorta," Cedars-Sinai Medical 
Center spokesman Ron Weiss said. 
</P>
<P>
 The man was not a guest at the North Highland Avenue hotel, said Los Angeles 
Police Lt. Eric Colter. There were no witnesses, but it did not appear that he 
was pushed, Colter said. 
</P>
