<HEADLINE>
<P>
HEALTH CARE: WAYS TO IMPROVE SERVICES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I was delighted to read in your February story "Operating Anew" that Santa 
Monica Hospital has joined with St. John's Hospital in planning how to expand 
health care services for the community on an individual and joint, cooperative 
basis. 
</P>
<P>
 I would urge housing for the growing number of seniors, in a sizable graying 
population, be part of the planning. 
</P>
<P>
 Short- and long-term care is a health care need that requires housing. A 
hospital-related elderly housing facility can supply the "preventive" health 
care so vital at this stage of life, and a family situation that builds on 
mutual assistance and friendships. 
</P>
<P>
 And as all elderly have a minimum of Social Security and Medicare aid for 
self-pay, such a housing program can also benefit the hospital as a financial 
resource. 
</P>
<P>
 Hyman Haves 
</P>
<P>
 Pacific Palisades  
</P>
