<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; INTERNATIONAL FAIR TO BE HELD AT SCHOOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An international cultural festival sponsored by a local private school is 
expected to draw hundreds of residents on Saturday, a spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Featuring food and entertainment from more than a dozen countries, the 
Heritage Day Fair will be held at St. Barbara School, 5306 W. McFadden Ave. The 
festival will be from 10 a.m. to 2 p.m. at the campus gymnasium, Principal 
Frances Sullivan said. 
</P>
<P>
 Countries represented will include Ireland, Vietnam, Germany, Mexico, England, 
Japan, Australia and others. For more information, call the school at (714) 
775-9477. -- JON NALICK 
</P>
</TEXT>
