<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS : THOUSAND OAKS; BUSINESSES SOUGHT FOR STUDENT 
PROGRAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BRENDA DAY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Conejo Valley Chamber of Commerce is looking for local business people 
willing to let a high school student spend the day with them on the job as part 
of a program designed to help students choose a future career. 
</P>
<P>
 Student Shadowing Day is expected to become an annual event, said Michal 
Orenstein, a career counselor helping to organize the May 17 event. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm looking for as many businesses to get involved as possible," Orenstein 
said. "The more, the merrier." 
</P>
<P>
 Selected Thousand Oaks students will be paired with hosts who work in career 
fields that the teen-agers have expressed an interest in pursuing after 
graduation, Orenstein said. For more information or to sign up, call 499-1993. 
BRENDA DAY 
</P>
</TEXT>
