<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LAGUNA NIGUEL; WATER SAFETY SKILLS CLASS TO BE OFFERED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A back-yard water safety class is being offered by the city's parks and 
recreation department. 
</P>
<P>
 The course will include teaching Red Cross water safety skills for infants and 
children. It also will cover how to prevent and be prepared for potential 
back-yard emergencies. 
</P>
<P>
 The class will meet on Mondays from 6:30 to 9:30 p.m., beginning Monday and 
running through April 4. Classroom instruction will be held at Fire Station No. 
5, at 23600 Pacific Island Drive, and pool classes will be held at the Crown 
Valley Community Park pool. 
</P>
<P>
 Cost is $30 per student. 
</P>
<P>
 Interested residents must register in person at Crown Valley Community Park, 
29751 Crown Valley Parkway. For more information, call (714) 362-4350. 
</P>
</TEXT>
