BASEBALL DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE MAJORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Baseball owners took a first step toward additional expansion by establishing 
a committee said adding teams probably was years away. 
</P>
<P>
 In a meeting at Scottsdale, Ariz., John Harrington of the Boston Red Sox was 
picked to head the panel, which won't make its initial report until this 
summer. Most owners say they won't consider expansion until a new labor 
agreement is reached with the players, making it unlikely new teams would start 
play until 1998, at the earliest. 
</P>
