<HEADLINE>
<P>
NHL ROUNDUP; RANGERS' ACE BEATS QUEBEC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Peter Andersson, playing in only his fifth game all season, scored his first 
goal since April 2 to break a 2-2 tie and had his first assist of the season to 
lead the Rangers in a 5-2 victory over the Quebec Nordiques in New York. 
</P>
<P>
 He is usually relegated to a role with the Rangers' Black Aces, five men who 
rarely play and usually watch from the upper boxes at Madison Square Garden. 
</P>
<P>
 "When I put the puck in, the first thing I did was to look up and point to the 
Black Aces," Andersson said. "I think those guys appreciated the fact that an 
Ace got the game-winner." 
</P>
<P>
 Winnipeg 4, Dallas 2 -- The Jets stopped their NHL-high 19-game winless streak 
at Winnipeg, getting goals from four different players to beat the Stars. 
</P>
<P>
 New Jersey 3, Florida 2 -- Stephane Richer scored with 5:27 to play as the 
Devils rallied with three consecutive goals at Miami. 
</P>
<P>
 Buffalo 7, Ottawa 2 -- Rookie defenseman Philippe Boucher scored two goals as 
the Sabres ended a two-game losing streak at Ottawa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
