<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; DOUBLES TEAMS PROVIDE VICTORY FOR VILLA PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The No. 1 doubles team of Brandon Louie and Eric Wu, and the No. 3 team of Jim 
Simpson and Leon Chien, won their sets for Villa Park in a 4-2 tiebreaker 
against Esperanza after a 9-9 nonleague boys' tennis match Wednesday at 
Esperanza High. 
</P>
<P>
 Single sets in singles and doubles decided the outcome in which Louie and Wu 
won, 7-5, and Simpson and Chien won, 9-7. Villa Park is 2-0 and Esperanza drops 
to 1-1. 
</P>
<P>
 In other nonleague boys' tennis: 
</P>
<P>
 Dana Hills 18, Laguna Beach 3 -- Freshman Brandon Fallon swept his singles 
sets, 7-5, 6-1, 6-2, for Dana Hills (1-0). Elliott West won two of the three 
sets for Laguna Beach (0-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine 14 1/3, Huntington Beach 6 2/3 -- Junior and No. 1 singles player Todd 
Harrington swept his sets for host Irvine (1-0), 6-0, 6-1, 6-0. 
</P>
<P>
 Servite 11 1/3, Valencia 9 2/3 -- No. 1 singles player Dan Lighthipe swept his 
opponents, 6-3, 6-0 and 6-0, for Servite (2-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Sunny Hills 13 2/3, Newport Harbor 7 1/3 -- No. 2 doubles team of Juno Quan 
and David Farkis swept their sets for Sunny Hills, 6-0, 6-3, 6-0. 
</P>
<P>
 Western 12 1/3, Los Amigos 8 2/3 -- Mack Sunthonlap swept his singles sets, 
6-1, 6-4, 6-2, for Western (1-0). 
</P>
