<HEADLINE>
<P>
DORSEY WINS BIG, RUINS CLEVELAND'S SECOND CHANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL LAZARUS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dorsey High guard Shewyn Morgan scored 17 points as the Dons spoiled Reseda 
Cleveland's second chance in the boys' basketball playoffs with a 70-59 win in 
a City Sction 4-A semifinal Wednesday night at Crenshaw High. 
</P>
<P>
 The Cavaliers were eliminated by Carson last Friday, but Carson was 
disqualified for using an ineligible player and Cleveland (15-7) was reinstated 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The Dons (18-8) went ahead for good with a 7-0 run in the second quarter for a 
37-31 halftime lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Dorsey will play Southern League rival Crenshaw in the 4-A final Saturday 
night. MICHAEL LAZARUS 
</P>
</TEXT>
