<P>
 It was a tough first year for Lappin. "We were a bunch of young pups and we 
got whipped," he said. Things should be better this season. Heck, even last 
season ended well. The Saxons beat El Dorado near the end of the season to 
avoid going winless in league play. They also scored eight runs in the seventh 
inning in the league finale against second-place Los Alamitos. They still lost, 
12-11. But Loara does return seven starters, who should help improve on last 
season's record. "We'll be better and we'll be competitive," Lappin said. 
Boomsma was a second-team all-league selection. Roncevich will probably be the 
No. 1 starter. Ortiz will get the first shot at the No. 2 slot. Ortiz played 
center field last season, but didn't pitch because he was coming off arm 
problems. He threw well over the summer. Ortiz and Hoffman were also 
second-team all-league selections. Hoffman is in his fourth year on the varsity 
and has been a starter at catcher the past two seasons. Kirkland, a reserve as 
a freshman last season, will be a key at shortstop. 
</P>
