<P>
 Bryant takes over this season, succeeding Rob Megill who resigned. Bryant 
played baseball at Cal State Fullerton and was a starter on the Titans' 
national championship team in 1984. He inherits a team that could do even 
better than its second-place finish of last season. They have a good nucleus of 
players and a terrific transfer in Bozman, who was at Bellflower a year ago. 
Bozman was a Times Orange County first-team selection as a running back in 
football and many believe his best sport is baseball. He is a solid hitter and 
has good speed. The infield is solid with Barnett, Blackledge and Taylor, who 
all are returning starters. Taylor hit .410 and scored 22 runs. Barnett, a 
starter since his sophomore season, had a team-high 26 runs batted in. He also 
scored 25 runs and had 18 stolen bases. The Griffins have a good group of young 
players to mix in. A lot will depend on pitchers Campbell and Cunningham. Both 
were on the varsity last season, so they have some experience. But one will 
have to step forward and be the ace. If one or both come through, then the 
Griffins will be tough to beat. 
