is, there's no one who can keep teams from pitching around Wright. He'll be 
more effective on the mound. Wright was 5-4 with 80 strikeouts and was named 
second-team All-Division I. Rojo returns as his catcher and Park is back at 
second base. David Reese, Mike Stevenson and Mike Villegas are seniors and one 
of them probably will end up as the No. 2 starter. The question is which one? 
For better or worse, they are all equal heading into the season. The Knights 
are depending on players with only junior varsity experience. A lot lower 
expectations this season, but, when Wright is on the mound, the Knights will be 
tough. 
