<P>
 The Golden Hawks missed the playoffs last season, a rarity. They had qualified 
in five of the previous six seasons. El Dorado should return this season. The 
Golden Hawks return four players who were first-team all-league 
selections--Cuevas, Flores, Moore and Reyes. Flores was 8-3 last season and is 
one of the top pitchers in the county. Reyes is an outstanding leadoff hitter. 
The infield should be solid, with Cuevas and Moore returning. The team has a 
good mixture of experience. A key will be how well Patterson develops at 
catcher. Because of injuries last season, the Golden Hawks went through three 
catchers, which hampered their pitching and allowed other teams to run wild. 
Patterson is talented, but he's a sophomore. Mike Castillo is another sophomore 
the Golden Hawks will depend on heavily. It might be a bit much to expect El 
Dorado to win the league title, but the playoffs are reachable. 
