<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: RESEDA'S CROSS NAMED NORTH VALLEY PLAYER OF YEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Reseda High point guard Trenton Cross has been selected North Valley League 
player of the year by a panel of coaches. 
</P>
<P>
 Cross, an All-City Section 3-A Division selection as a junior, averaged 17.4 
points before suffering a broken bone in his foot three weeks ago.He has signed 
a letter of intent to play next season at Cal State Northridge. 
</P>
<P>
 Mark Sebek of Nordhoff, Damien Cantrell of Santa Clara and Manuel Escamilla of 
Santa Paula shared the player of the year award in the Frontier League. 
</P>
<P>
 Sebek, a 6-foot-2 senior guard, averaged 24.5 points, 10.7 rebounds, five 
assists and 2.8 steals per game. He is Nordhoff's second all-time leading 
scorer (1,411 points). 
</P>
<P>
 Cantrell, a 6-4 senior forward, averaged 21 points, 8.2 rebounds and two 
steals for the league-champion Saints. Escamilla, a 6-1 junior guard, averaged 
17.8 points and four rebounds. Golf 
</P>
<P>
 Nationally renowned golf architect Tom Fazio has been hired to design the 
Farmont Golf Club, a course to be constructed near Ojai. Construction is 
expected to begin this year and be completed by 1995. 
</P>
<P>
 Fazio's firm has overseen the remodeling of such acclaimed courses as 
Inverness Golf Club in Ohio and Oak Hill Golf Club in New York. 
</P>
<P>
 Southern California courses designed by Fazio include Pelican Hill Golf Club 
in Orange County and The Vintage Course in Palm Springs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
