<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Southwestern 76, Moorpark 73 -- Sixth-seeded Moorpark rallied from a 12-point 
second-half deficit and had a chance to tie with 10 seconds remaining, but Sean 
Martin's three-point shot fell short in a second-round Southern California 
regional game. 
</P>
<P>
 Paul Foster led Moorpark with 17 points and Martin added 15.Rod Stinson (12 
points) and Jaime Jaquez (10) also scored in double figures for Moorpark 
(24-9). 
</P>
<P>
 Chaffey 85, Canyons 77 -- Despite having four starters score in double 
figures, the Cougars (15-17) proved to be no match for Chaffey (30-5) in a 
Southern California regional playoff game at Ontario. 
</P>
<P>
 Kwesi Fulton had 18 points and 10 rebounds for Canyons. Bryan Camacho added 17 
points, Alric Gillette had 14 and Randy Eason contributed 10 points and eight 
assists. BASEBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Northwood 14, The Master's 12 -- The Mustangs (5-7-2) blew a five-run lead 
over the final four innings in a nonconference game at Master's. 
</P>
<P>
 Matt Henzie went three for five with five runs batted in, including a grand 
slam that gave Master's a 12-7 lead in the fifth. 
</P>
<P>
 L.A. City 5, Mission 2 -- John Toven had two hits and Francisco Flores added 
two hits and a two-run double for Mission in a Southern California Conference 
game at L.A. City. MEN'S TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
 Cal Lutheran 8, Occidental 1 -- Graduate student Tony Cohen, an All-American 
for Cal Lutheran in 1990, defeated Occidental's Pete Bassett, 6-2, 6-1, in No. 
1 singles to key the victory in a Southern California Intercollegiate Athletic 
Conference match. 
</P>
