<HEADLINE>
<P>
INSIDE LINE: OC HIGH: STUDENT NEWS & VIEWS; CASTING CALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 High school students of Hispanic descent are invited to participate in a play 
commemorating the 20th anniversary of the 80-foot-long MEChA Mural at Nealley 
Library at Rancho Santiago Community College's Santa Ana campus.(A portion of 
the mural is pictured above.) 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Santiago graduate Louie Olivos Jr. wrote the play about the mural and 
its creation two decades ago. The play will be performed during Cinco de Mayo 
festivities at the college. The Movimiento Estudiantil Chicano de Atzlan is a 
student organization that focuses on Chicano culture and history. 
</P>
<P>
 Students interested in being in the play should call Olivos at (714) 543-5598. 
Rehearsals will be Tuesday evenings and Saturday mornings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
