<HEADLINE>
<P>
INSIDE LINE: TO GO OR NOT TO GO; OC HIGH: STUDENT NEWS & VIEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By OC Live 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 What's the big deal about Shakespeare? Figuring that a lot of teens are 
interested in the answer to that question, a special one-hour production of 
excerpts of his works is being presented at Golden West Community College. . 
The show features 30 actors, including high school and college theater 
students."All the World's a Stage: Shakespeare's Monologues," will feature 
scenes or soliloquies from five of Shakespeare's best-known works -- "Hamlet, 
Prince of Denmark," "Macbeth," "As You Like It," "The Merchant of Venice" and 
"Romeo and Juliet." 
</P>
<P>
 Performances will be at 8 p.m. March 8 and 9. at Golden West College Community 
Theater, 15744 Golden West St., Huntington Beach. Admission is free. (714) 
895-8772. 
</P>
</TEXT>
