METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: CERRITOS; 
SUPERINTENDENT LUCAS PUT ON INDEFINITE PAID LEAVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The ABC Unified District School Board has put embattled Supt. Larry L. Lucas 
on paid leave indefinitely. 
</P>
<P>
 Board President Cecy Groom offered no explanation for the move Tuesday night 
and the superintendent left the district's headquarters before the announcement 
was made.Board members then named Deputy Supt. Ira Toibin to replace Lucas 
until further notice. 
</P>
<P>
 Lucas has headed the district since 1988. In July, the school board voted to 
extend his contract another year, to June, 1997, and to increase his pay by 
about $1,000, to $109,168. 
</P>
<P>
 But recently Lucas has clashed with a new majority, backed by the teachers 
union, that gained control of the school board in November after an 11-day 
teachers strike. Some board members had asked Lucas privately to leave about a 
month ago but he refused, his attorney, David C. Larsen, said. 
</P>
