<HEADLINE>
<P>
TOPICS / TAXES; FREE AID FOR FILERS WITH SPECIAL NEEDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KIMBERLY BRAASCH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Free income-tax assistance is available in Long Beach and several Southeast 
cities for low-income taxpayers, senior citizens, the disabled and 
non-English-speaking residents. 
</P>
<P>
 The assistance will be provided by volunteers trained by the Internal Revenue 
Service and the California Franchise Tax Board. Most of the sites will remain 
open until April 15. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents should bring current tax records and last year's tax returns. A 
Spanish version of Form 1040A and instructions will be available at all sites. 
Volunteers from many sites may go to residences of shut-ins to provide tax 
assistance.  
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call the IRS at (800) 829-1040. Hearing-impaired 
taxpayers may call (800) 829-4059. 
</P>
