By Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 U.S. and Vietnamese negotiators have agreed in principle on the opening of 
liaison offices and on U.S. war claims against Vietnam, the Hanoi government 
said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 A statement issued by the Foreign Ministry said two days of talks, critical 
steps in establishing diplomatic relations, ended "with a very positive 
result."The statement said more meetings will be held later to finalize the 
agreements. 
</P>
