"productive exchange of views" in New York on human rights -- marked a 
promising start to a new chapter in ties opened when Washington scrapped the 
19-year economic embargo against Vietnam. 
</P>
<P>
 The liaison offices in Hanoi and Washington will be upgraded to embassies if 
relations continue to improve, officials have said. 
