<P>
 Litton Posts Second-Quarter Loss: Litton Industries reported a $151.3-million 
loss due to spinning off its non-defense businesses.The loss for the three 
months ended Jan. 31, the equivalent of $3.32 per share, came on sales of $804 
million. That was up from $754 million a year earlier on comparable defense 
electronics and shipbuilding operations. Litton recorded $174.7 million in 
special charges for splitting off its energy exploration data and automated 
assembly line businesses into a separate company. Setting aside the charge for 
discontinued operations, Litton's profit rose 27% during the quarter. Litton 
attributed the higher operating earnings to reduced interest expenses, improved 
sales of advanced electronics and a strong performance in Navy shipbuilding. 
