<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: NEWPORT BEACH; CITY REIMBURSED FOR MEASURE A EXPENSES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB ELSTON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city has been reimbursed $35,239 for the cost of a citywide special 
election last November on the controversial Measure A.  
</P>
<P>
 The Irvine Co. and the Newport Conservancy last year agreed to pay for the 
cost of the election.Voters were asked to decide whether to purchase 138 acres 
of prime acreage near the Upper Newport Bay for $68 million. 
</P>
<P>
 Earlier this month, the Irvine Co. paid its half and on Monday, the Newport 
Conservancy paid its portion, said Councilwoman Jean H. Watt, who is also 
president of the environmental group. 
</P>
<P>
 "It is nice to have it done," Watt said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Measure A lost by a wide margin -- about 65% of Newport voters opposed the 
plan.BOB ELSTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
