<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: IRVINE; UCI NAMES INTERIM HUMANITIES DEAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Michael Clark has been named acting dean of the UC Irvine School of 
Humanities. 
</P>
<P>
 Clark, who specializes in Colonial American literature, has been a member of 
the UCI faculty since 1983.He now serves as chairman of the Department of 
English and Comparative Literature. He earned a doctorate in English from UCI 
in 1977 and taught for several years at the University of Michigan. 
</P>
<P>
 Also, Steven Carter was appointed chairman of the East Asian Languages and 
Literature Department. 
</P>
<P>
 Carter has been a professor at UCI since 1990 and is a former Fulbright 
scholar. He has written several books on Japanese literature. 
</P>
<P>
 Carter replaces Pauline Yu, who moved to UCLA this year to become of the dean 
of humanities in the College of Letters and Science. 
</P>
</TEXT>
