<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO; 5 PRINCIPALS NAMED FOR NEXT SCHOOL 
YEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RICHARD CORE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Five principals have been named to head elementary schools in the Capistrano 
Unified School District for the 1994-95 school year. The five are: 
</P>
<P>
 * Dianne Hoff, Wood Canyon Elementary, Aliso Viejo.Hoff comes from 
Cartersville, Ga., where she was principal of Cartersville Elementary School. 
She holds bachelor's and master's degrees in secondary English education from 
Indiana University and is a doctoral candidate in education administration at 
the University of Louisville. 
</P>
<P>
 * Susan MacConaghy, Barcelona Hills Elementary, Mission Viejo. MacConaghy is 
currently the principal of Mission Elementary School in Redlands. She holds a 
bachelor's degree in English from UC Santa Barbara and a master's degree in 
education from USC. She is working on a doctorate in education administration 
at USC. 
</P>
<P>
 * Deborah McCormick, George L. White Elementary, Laguna Niguel. Currently 
principal of Jefferson Elementary School in the Santa Ana Unified School 
District, McCormick holds a bachelor's degree in elementary education from Ohio 
State University and a master's degree in curriculum and instruction and 
education administration from Cal State Long Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 * Aida Nunez, San Juan Elementary, San Juan Capistrano. Nunez has been 
assistant principal of Fremont Elementary School in the Santa Ana Unified 
School District. She holds a bachelor's degree in Spanish from UC Irvine and a 
master's degree in administration from United States International University. 
</P>
<P>
 * Curt Visca, Bathgate Elementary, Mission Viejo. Currently the assistant 
principal at Bergeson Elementary School in Laguna Niguel, Visca is known as the 
creator and star of "It's Curtoon Time," a local cable television program. 
Bathgate will open the year as a visual arts academy. Visca holds a bachelor's 
degree in advertising from Cal State Fullerton and a master's degree in 
education administration from National University. RICHARD CORE 
</P>
</TEXT>
