<HEADLINE>
<P>
JUNIOR HIGH TEACHER CHARGED IN MOLESTATION OF FORMER STUDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK I. PINSKY, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Kraemer Junior High School teacher has been charged with molesting a 
14-year-old boy, court officials confirmed Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Michelle Lynn Smith, 36, of Orange was arrested by Placentia police at 12:20 
a.m. on Feb. 26, department spokeswoman Corinne Loomis said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police had received an anonymous phone call regarding "possibly suspicious" 
activity in a parked car in the 1600 block of Sierra Madre Circle, Loomis said. 
</P>
<P>
 When officers arrived, they made contact with two people in the car -- Smith 
and a 14-year-old boy, Loomis said. Smith was arrested on suspicion of child 
molestation and booked at County Jail. She later posted $50,000 bail. 
</P>
<P>
 The alleged victim, a former student of Smith's, was not placed in protective 
custody, Loomis said. 
</P>
<P>
 As required by state law, Smith was "assigned to home duty" after her arrest, 
said Tim Van Eck, assistant superintendent of the Placentia-Yorba Linda Unified 
School District. Smith will continue to be paid pending the outcome of an 
investigation based on the criminal case, Van Eck said. 
</P>
<P>
 Smith faces eight charges of child molestation. Her arraignment is scheduled 
for March 28 in Municipal Court in Fullerton. All of the felony counts 
pertained to one youth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
