<HEADLINE>
<P>
ARMORED TRUCK'S GUARD IS ROBBED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An man disguised in a postal uniform robbed an armored truck guard Wednesday 
as he was making a delivery at the American First Federal Credit Union, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The man entered the credit union in the 6800 block of Knott Avenue about 10:30 
a.m., according to Sgt. Robert R. Chaney Jr. A few minutes later, a transport 
company guard with a money bag walked into the bank and was confronted by the 
robber, who displayed a semiautomatic handgun and ordered the guard to the 
floor. 
</P>
<P>
 The robber fled with the money in what police believe was a late 1980s Honda 
Accord. 
</P>
