 Fluor Chairman OK After Surgery: Les McCraw, chairman and chief executive 
officer of Fluor Corp., had surgery Wednesday to remove a small, malignant 
tumor from his prostate gland.A spokeswoman for the engineering and 
construction company said McCraw was listed in good condition and "his 
prognosis for a full recovery is excellent." McCraw is expected to return to 
work by the end of the month. Fluor's annual shareholders meeting will take 
place Tuesday as scheduled, the company said. 
