<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: RESTAURANTS / RETAIL; RETAILER GIVES MORE THAN JUST A THOUGHT TO 
DISABLED AND INJURED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Greg Johnson / Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Just A Thought, a new retail business at Fashion Island in Newport Beach, 
sells gift baskets through an outdoor cart at the shopping mall. 
</P>
<P>
 Just A Thought is more than a business, however. It was created with the help 
of a grant from the Department of Rehabilitation and the Alternative Training & 
Learning Center, a nonprofit agency that helps people with disabilities and 
internal head injuries. 
</P>
<P>
 Just A Thought provides an "integrated work environment" for both disabled and 
non-disabled people, according to Wendy Garrison, manager of Fashion Island's 
specialty retail programs. "It teaches them, step by step, how to become 
self-sufficient and active within the business community." 
</P>
</TEXT>
