<P>
MORELLI'S II INC. LOSES 6 CENTS A SHARE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nona Morelli's II Inc., an Irvine Italian food company, said it lost $304,355, 
or 6 cents a share, for the second fiscal quarter ended Dec. 31, compared to a 
loss of $177,798, or 36 cents a share, a year earlier.Per-share figures were 
adjusted to reflect a December 1-for-10 reverse stock split. Revenue rose to 
$818,808 from $439,516. For the first half of the fiscal year, the company lost 
$2.8 million, or 63 cents a share. 
