<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SAN GABRIEL VALLEY; 30-HOUR FAST RAISES HUNGER-RELIEF FUNDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 More than 3,000 people in the San Gabriel Valley area participated last week 
in World Vision's annual "30-Hour Famine," an international hunger education 
program. 
</P>
<P>
 In a symbolic gesture, groups from Pasadena Covenant Church and Duarte High 
School fasted for 30 hours Friday and Saturday and accepted pledge 
contributions for each hour they went without food. Last year, a million 
teen-agers worldwide raised more than $15 million for hunger programs. 
</P>
<P>
 During the fast, some groups arranged sleep-overs with hunger education 
programs or with food service at homeless shelters. 
</P>
