<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SAN MARINO ; SUPERINTENDENT HIRED FROM NEWPORT MESA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 50-year-old assistant superintendent for the Newport Mesa Unified District 
has been appointed superintendent of schools for San Marino. 
</P>
<P>
 Thomas Godley was selected last week by the Board of Education after a 
unanimous vote. Godley, chosen after an extensive statewide search, will assume 
his new position March 28. 
</P>
<P>
 At Newport Mesa, Godley was responsible for budget, facilities and support 
services, and was also the district's chief labor negotiator. He has a master's 
degree in English literature and a doctorate in educational administration from 
USC. 
</P>
<P>
 Godley has signed a three-year contract with the district and will be paid 
$87,500 annually. He is married and has a 23-year-old son. 
</P>
</TEXT>
